01:20.581 --> 01:21.422
The Lord has spoken, right?

01:22.002 --> 01:22.723
So he just starts.

01:22.743 --> 01:28.050
Here's my vision, God has spoken, and the Lord God has spoken concerning Edom.

01:29.058 --> 01:34.828
And just out of nowhere, the first verse, hey, this is not about Israel, this is not about Judah, this is about Edom.

01:35.489 --> 01:36.871
We've heard a rumor from the Lord.

01:37.512 --> 01:39.055
An ambassador is sent among the heathen.

01:39.716 --> 01:42.581
Arise ye and let us rise up against her in battle.

01:43.342 --> 01:47.489
Have made thee small among the heathen, thou art greatly despised.

01:48.191 --> 01:54.962
The pride of thine heart hath deceived thee, thou that dwellest in the clefs of the rock, whose habitation is high.

01:55.554 --> 02:09.042
that saith in his heart, who shall bring me down to the ground, and though thou exalt thyself as the eagle, and though thou saith thy nest among the stars, thence will I bring thee down saith the Lord."

02:09.062 --> 02:14.674
A lot more we're going to look at tonight, but I think you can tell by the opening verses, God is not happy with Edom.

02:14.978 --> 02:22.610
