17:03.212 --> 17:11.841
But while the Philistines are attacking and while the Arabians are attacking, Edom would have been better off to just humble themselves and say, hey, maybe they're getting what they deserve, but I'm not going to say anything.

17:11.861 --> 17:15.986
But instead, they want to participate and God is bringing judgment upon Edom.

17:16.898 --> 17:19.221
Obadiah mentions another nation for judgment.

17:19.281 --> 17:23.647
Jonah, we'll talk about in a few weeks, also brings judgment against another nation, the Assyrians.

17:24.749 --> 17:26.050
Nahum would do the same thing.

17:27.292 --> 17:30.156
The key phrase for the book of Obadiah sort of helps us remember it.

17:30.917 --> 17:32.459
Yes, you are your brother's keeper.

17:33.721 --> 17:40.450
Yes, you have responsibility to your brother, Jacob, not to rejoice when he's in turmoil, but to come to his aid and you didn't do that.

17:40.990 --> 17:42.813
