30:17.997 --> 30:20.881
There's not too many books that are 2,800 years old that I read for fun.

30:23.184 --> 30:25.908
I'm not trying to find ancient books just to read to pass the time.

30:26.989 --> 30:30.674
The Word of God is a living book, which makes it timeless.

30:31.138 --> 30:36.824
And so these events that happened 2,800 years ago are still relevant for us as New Testament believers today.

30:36.865 --> 30:37.665
What are some takeaways?

30:38.546 --> 30:39.267
Here's a few of them.

30:39.287 --> 30:43.672
Number one, let's never forget to let God determine our significance.

30:45.635 --> 30:47.116
Eden thought they could determine their own.

30:47.176 --> 30:48.518
They lifted themselves up in pride.

30:48.558 --> 30:52.062
And God says, when you try to lift yourself up in pride, I've got to put you down.

30:52.082 --> 30:54.324
But if you just humble yourself, I'll exalt you in due time.

30:55.185 --> 30:57.788
Let's let God be the one who determines our significance, not us.

30:58.669 --> 30:59.250
Number two,

31:00.130 --> 31:03.095
